Here&#x27;s an example which might explain the decoupling a bit:<p><pre><code>    // You may call this syntactic sugar
    var p1 = new Promise(function(response, reject) {
        setTimeout(function(){ 
            response(Math.random() * 1000); 
        });
    }).then(function(val){ console.log(val); return val; });

    // But here&#x27;s the magical decoupled call
    p1.then(function(val) { console.log(val); });</code></pre>
